First Lady Melania Trump visited Lily's Place, the first nonprofit infant recovery center in the nation, in Huntington, West Virginia. She was accompanied by Dr. Elinor McCance-Katz, assistant secretary for mental health and substance use at the Department of Health and Human Services, and Kellyanne Conway, counselor to the President. During the visit, they participated in a roundtable discussion with staff and a graduate of the program. Mrs. Trump also toured the facility and spoke with two families currently enrolled in the program. She praised the passion and commitment of the founders and staff at Lily's Place, emphasizing the importance of supporting the whole family in order to give infants born dependent on drugs the best opportunity to thrive. Mrs. Trump expressed hope for creating more opportunities like Lily's Place to help infants and children grow into happy, healthy adults.